===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|hold|lang=enm}}, {{term|holde|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|hold||gracious, friendly, kind, favorable, true, faithful, loyal, devout, acceptable, pleasant|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|hulþaz|favourable, gracious, loyal|lang=en}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|kel-|to tend, incline, bend, tip|lang=en}}. Cognate with {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|hold||gracious, friendly, synpathetic, grateful|lang=de}}, {{etyl|da|-}} and {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|huld||fair, kindly, gracious|lang=da|lang=sv}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|hollur||faithful, dedicated, loyal|lang=is}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|Huld||grace, favour|lang=de}}.

